# Trivy IaC ignore file for the terraform/infra stack.
# Phase 2 of docs/0.10.x/iac-quality-gates-plan.md. Full rationale and
# per-id classification + target versions are in terraform/infra/BASELINE.md.
#
# NOTE on coarseness: Trivy ignores by rule ID, not per resource, so an id
# listed here is suppressed everywhere in the stack (a new resource that
# violates an already-listed rule would not be caught). Acceptable for this
# small, slow-changing stack; the must-fix ids below are removed as Phase 2.5
# lands, and the Phase 3 drift check flags any id here that no longer matches.

# --- CMK class: permanent, design-driven suppression -------------------
# Every flagged resource is already encrypted at rest with an AWS-managed
# or service-default key; these rules demand a customer-managed KMS key,
# whose control benefits a solo operator cannot exploit, at per-key cost.
# Cabalmail keeps AWS-default at-rest encryption. See BASELINE.md / CHANGELOG.
# AWS-0025 (DynamoDB SSE) cleared in 0.10.x: the cabal-counter table
# was the only table without an explicit server_side_encryption block.
AWS-0017  # CloudWatch log groups should use a CMK
AWS-0033  # ECR repository should use a CMK
AWS-0132  # S3 encryption should use a CMK
AWS-0136  # SNS topic should use a CMK (it is encrypted with the aws/sns managed key)

# --- Other design-driven suppressions (permanent) ----------------------
AWS-0104  # Unrestricted egress: ECS tasks and the NAT instance need broad outbound (image pulls, DNS, SMTP delivery) via NAT
AWS-0320  # S3 bucket names not DNS-compliant: names are stable identifiers; renaming means a data migration
AWS-0178  # VPC flow logs disabled: deliberate cost choice, consistent with monitoring being off in every environment
AWS-0190  # API Gateway response caching disabled: caching is undesirable for this mailbox API

# --- Must-fix in Phase 2.5 (all cleared) -------------------------------
# AWS-0031 (ECR mutable) fixed in the safe batch; AWS-0095 (SNS unencrypted),
# AWS-0096 (SQS unencrypted), and AWS-0131 (NAT EBS unencrypted) fixed in the
# 2.5 remainder. Encrypting the SNS topic with the managed key moved it to
# AWS-0136 in the CMK suppression above.

# --- Decay: low/medium hygiene, walk down over time --------------------
# AWS-0024 (DynamoDB PITR) cleared in 0.10.x: every table now enables
# point_in_time_recovery (the counter table was the last holdout).
AWS-0090  # S3 data versioning (transient cache/artifact buckets)
AWS-0089  # S3 bucket access logging
AWS-0066  # Lambda X-Ray tracing
AWS-0124  # Security group rule missing description
AWS-0003  # API Gateway X-Ray tracing
